                <h1>Kaiser Permanente: A Brief History of Healthcare Innovation</h1>
                <p>Kaiser Permanente, founded in 1945, emerged from plans initiated by Dr. Sidney Garfield and industrialist Henry J. Kaiser during World War II. Initially established to provide healthcare for wartime workers, it grew into a non-profit health system offering a wide range of services, emphasizing preventive care and integrated health delivery. Today, it's one of the largest managed healthcare organizations, pioneering in health education and innovative care models.</p>
